<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-10-29T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-10-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="92" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d92">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War
                                1939/16294</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">Memorandum of Conversation, by the Secretary of
                                    State</hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-10-29">October 29,
                                        1941</date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>The British Ambassador called at his request. He brought up the
                                Finnish question and stated that Russia desired Great Britain to
                                declare war against Finland. I disposed of the matter by saying that
                                on yesterday I had sent a strong message to the Finnish Government
                                bringing this matter as nearly to a sharp focus as possible short of
                                a breach of relations, and paving the way for any further action at
                                any time. This seemed to satisfy the Ambassador for the present.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>C[<hi rend="smallcaps">ordell</hi>] H[<hi rend="smallcaps">ull</hi>]</signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>